					<head>Commentary</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597" rend="visible">
						<summary>A fragment of Judeo-Arabic commentary of Japheth ben Ali ha-Levi on Deuteronomy 1:1-7:10.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he" otherLangs="jrb">Hebrew, Judeo-Arabic</textLang>
						<msItem n="0" rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597">
							<locus from="1r" to="92v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Perush devarim</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">פרוש דברים</title>
							<note>
								<p>Concerns Deut. 1:1-7:10.</p>
								<p>The unpointed text of Deut. 1:1-6:1 and 6:6-7:10 is embodied, followed by the Arabic translation.</p>
								<p>Chapters 1:1-2:21, 3:24, 4:7, 29-30 are pointed, the rest is unpointed.</p>
								<p>The volume has been collated.</p>
							</note>
							<author key="http://viaf.org/viaf/54984961">
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/54984961" xml:lang="en">Japheth ben Ali, ha-Levi,‏ active 10th century </persName>
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/54984961" xml:lang="he">יפת בן עלי, הלוי</persName>
							</author>
							<filiation>Cf. a similar handwriting of <ref target="Margoliouth_1965" type="number">271</ref> and <ref target="Margoliouth_1965" type="number">275</ref>, the latter being dated <date calendar="Gregorian">1603</date>.</filiation>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex, square and semi-cursive script of 15th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper codex</support>
								<extent>92 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>206</height>
										<width>148</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>183</height>
										<width>125</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>92 folios (+ 2 paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>10 quires, of mostly 10 leaves each, apart from the first which has only 4 leaves.</p>
									<p>Quires signed with Hebrew letters and Arabic words on the upper margin of the first page, and with Hebrew letters on the lower margin of the last page.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>6th and 10th quire are imperfect; lacunae after folios 53 and 84.</p>
									<p>Slightly water-damaged.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="23" writtenLines="23">
									<p>The Hebrew biblical text is embodied.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
